1. Introduction {#sec1-nutrients-10-01451}
===============

The gastrointestinal tract plays a central role in determining appetite, energy intake, and postprandial glycemic excursions \[[@B1-nutrients-10-01451]\]. It acts as a complex interface between ingested nutrients and the body’s metabolic responses, integrating signals from mechanical, chemical, and hormonal pathways to regulate digestion, absorption, and satiety \[[@B2-nutrients-10-01451]; [@B3-nutrients-10-01451]\]. Disruptions in these processes can contribute to the development of metabolic disorders such as obesity and type 2 diabetes. Understanding the mechanisms by which the gastrointestinal tract influences appetite and glycemic control is therefore critical for developing effective nutritional and therapeutic strategies.

