============

About 100 million men worldwide are suggested to be subfertile ([@ref19]), but for many of them an accurate diagnostic cause remains elusive. The ability of sperm to successfully migrate through the female reproductive tract is the key to natural fertilization; however, current techniques for assessing sperm motility track cell head locations without analysis of the beating flagellum, and thus lack mechanistic insight.

